.SH NAME
TextDecoderStream.fatal \- TextDecoderStream: fatal property
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]fatal\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]TextDecoderStream\f[R] interface is a \f[CR]boolean\f[R]
indicating if the error mode of the \f[CR]TextDecoderStream\f[R] object
is set to \f[CR]fatal\f[R].
.PP
If the property is \f[CR]true\f[R] then a decoder will throw a
\f[CR]TypeError\f[R] if it encounters malformed data while decoding.
If \f[CR]false\f[R] the decoder will substitute the invalid data with
the replacement character \f[CR]U+FFFD\f[R] (ï¿½).
The value of the property is set in the \f[CR]TextDecoderStream()\f[R]
constructor.
.SH VALUE
A \f[CR]boolean\f[R] which will return \f[CR]true\f[R] if the error mode
is set to \[lq]fatal\[rq].
Otherwise it returns \f[CR]false\f[R], indicating that the error mode is
\[lq]replacement\[rq].
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
stream = \f[B]new\f[R] TextDecoderStream();
